    "notes": "The single ambient loop that plays over the drawing sequence. 26.67 seconds at 72 BPM 4/4, which is the design tempo the rhythm-input in FifthSeasonBeach.gd runs against. Two-note phrases on the piano voice, a held cello note under, a bell chime on beat 1 of every second bar (bars 1, 3, 5, 7).\n\nAuthored so bar 1 downbeat lines up with the metronome pulse in the game; the rhythm-drawing player will feel the loop as their beat clock."
